1 B. An application that raises an unexhausted claim shall establish all of the
2 following:
3 (1) That the petitioner had good cause for failing to raise the claim in prior
4 post-conviction applications.
5 (2) That the claim is not plainly without merit.
6 (3) That the petitioner has not intentionally engaged in any dilatory litigation
7 tactics.
8 C. The failure of the petitioner to satisfy any requirement in Paragraph A or
9 B of this Article shall result in dismissal of the application.
10 D. The provisions of Article 927.1 shall apply to any application that is filed
11 pursuant to this Article.
12 E. The state district court shall expedite its consideration and resolution of
13 an unexhausted claim.
14 F. If any party invokes the supervisory jurisdiction of the Louisiana Supreme
15 Court to review the state district court's resolution of the unexhausted claim, the
16 Louisiana Supreme Court shall give priority consideration to and expedite its review
17 of the claim.
